attributes.PROJECT_FULL_TITLE: Interconnection between Sicily (IT) and Tunisia node (TN) [currently known as "ELMED"]
attributes.TECHNICAL_DESCR: The project consists of a new HVDC interconnection in VSC technology between Tunisia and Italy, with a rated power of 600 MW. The link will be developed between the converter stations of Partanna in Sicily (IT) and Mlaabi on the Cape Bon peninsula (TN), for a total length of approximately 220 km long (mainly in submarine cable) and a maximum depth of approximately 800 meters.
attributes.PROMOTERS: Terna S.p.A. - Rete Elettrica Nazionale (IT) ; STEG - Société Tunisienne de l'Electricité et du Gaz (TN)
